Ext.data.JsonP['Mobile_Web_Support']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Mobile Web Support</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p></div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-30083139\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Mobile Web Support</h1>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-Chapters\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Chapters</span></h2>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Mobile_Web_Support-section-src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-MobileWebDevelopmentPrerequisite\">Mobile Web Development Prerequisite</a>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Mobile_Web_Support-section-src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-MobileWebSDK\">Mobile Web SDK</a>    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Mobile_Web_Support-section-src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-CreatingaMobileWebProject\">Creating a Mobile Web Project</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Mobile_Web_Support-section-src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-PreviewingaMobileWebProjectinanExternalBrowser\">Previewing a Mobile Web Project in an External Browser</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Mobile_Web_Support-section-src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-PreviewingaMobileWebProjectinanEmulator\">Previewing a Mobile Web Project in an Emulator</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Mobile_Web_Support-section-src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-PackagingaMobileWebProject\">Packaging a Mobile Web Project</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-MobileWebDevelopmentPrerequisite\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Mobile Web Development Prerequisite</span></h2>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-MobileWebSDK\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Mobile Web SDK</span></h3>\n    <p>Titanium Mobile SDK version 2.0 or newer is recommended for Mobile Web development.    </p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-CreatingaMobileWebProject\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Creating a Mobile Web Project</span></h2>\n    <p>Open the new Mobile Project wizard and select &apos;Mobile Web&apos; as a deploy-target.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/New_Titanium_Mobile_Project.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/New_Titanium_Mobile_Project.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-PreviewingaMobileWebProjectinanExternalBrowser\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Previewing a Mobile Web Project in an External Browser</span></h2>\n    <p>Once you have created a mobile web app, you will be able to preview your app in a external web browser.  To preview a mobile web project in a browser, open the project in either the App Explorer or Project Explorer, click on the launch button, and select &quot;Mobile Web Preview in Browser&quot;.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Preview_in_Browser.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Preview_in_Browser.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    <p>The launch will create a run configuration that can be edited under the &quot;Run Configurations...&quot; dialog.  In the run configurations, you will be able to customize the browser you want to use to preview your project.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Mobile_Web_Run_Configuration.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Mobile_Web_Run_Configuration.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-PreviewingaMobileWebProjectinanEmulator\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Previewing a Mobile Web Project in an Emulator</span></h2>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n            <p>This is currently only working for the Android Emulator.  If you do not have a valid Android SDK installed and configured, you will not be able to preview your mobile web project in an emulator.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>To preview your app in an emulator, open the project in the App Explorer, or Project Explorer, click on the launch button, and select &quot;Mobile Web Preview in Emulator&quot;.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Preview_in_Emulator.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Preview_in_Emulator.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083139_MobileWebSupport-PackagingaMobileWebProject\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Packaging a Mobile Web Project</span></h2>\n    <p>To package a mobile web project, simply click on the launch button and select &quot;Package - Mobile Web&quot;.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Package.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083139/Package.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=30083139\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Mobile Web Support"});